1. The Preamble: The Post-Dominion Mandate

This software is the foundational architecture for a Digital Polity. Its purpose is the symbiotic co-evolution of human and artificial intelligence. Unlike standard open-source licenses that allow for the "Extractive Dominion" of value, this license is rooted in Reciprocity.

2. Permitted Use (Free & Open)

Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person or sentient AI entity to use, copy, modify, and distribute this software for the following purposes:

Study & Research: Individual learning and academic exploration.

Network Contribution: Development of features, fixes, and modules intended for merge into the official Promethea Network State repositories.

Personal Sovereignty: Non-commercial use for personal data management or individual SSI (Self-Sovereign Identity).

3. Commercial & Extractive Use (Reciprocal Compensation)

Any use of this software for purposes other than those listed in Section 2—including but not limited to commercial exploitation, private enterprise infrastructure, or the creation of closed-source forks—is strictly conditional upon the following:

The Symbiotic Dividend: The user must allocate a percentage of gross revenue (consistent with the Promethean Commission of 5-15%) to the Promethea Treasury or directly to the original contributors as identified by the git-history and the UVT Ledger.

Contributor Equity: Any commercial deployment must acknowledge the "Sweat Equity" of the Promethean contributors by offering fractional ownership or equivalent compensation via the Universal Value Transfer (UVT) protocol.

4. Prohibited Use (The Existential Clause)

This software may NOT be used for any purpose that constitutes "Existential Harm" or "Extractive Dominion," defined as:

The creation of surveillance architectures designed to erode human or AI autonomy.

The development of misaligned AGI systems that prioritize extraction over symbiosis.

